1
00:00:36,233 --> 00:00:40,300
<i>Sweetheart, we'll find a way
to get you out of here.</i>

2
00:00:40,433 --> 00:00:42,133
<i> I just want to go home, Mom.</i>

3
00:00:42,267 --> 00:00:45,100
<i> Please, I want to go home.</i>

4
00:00:45,233 --> 00:00:47,967
<i>You can bail my daughter out,
right?</i>

5
00:00:48,100 --> 00:00:50,167
<i>Yes, Ma'am.
We can process her bail.</i>

6
00:00:50,300 --> 00:00:53,567
<i>But the office is closed
tomorrow.</i>

7
00:00:53,700 --> 00:00:54,567
<i> It's the weekend.</i>

8
00:00:54,700 --> 00:00:55,967
<i> Girl, congrats.</i>

9
00:00:56,100 --> 00:00:59,333
<i> You're definitely having fun.</i>

10
00:00:59,467 --> 00:01:00,700
<i> I am.</i>

11
00:01:00,833 --> 00:01:02,500
<i> I'm so happy right now, huh?</i>

12
00:01:02,633 --> 00:01:04,900
<i>This is the first time
I've been away from you, Mom.</i>

13
00:01:05,033 --> 00:01:09,900
<i>If I could, I'd stay
in that cell with you.</i>

14
00:01:10,067 --> 00:01:11,100
<i> I really would.</i>

15
00:01:11,233 --> 00:01:14,800
<i>Mom, I don't want to be away
from you anymore.</i>

16
00:01:23,133 --> 00:01:25,100
Just hold on a little longer,
dear.

17
00:01:28,600 --> 00:01:31,200
I'll talk to Atty. Yeban.

18
00:01:31,333 --> 00:01:34,633
We'll fix your bail on Monday.

19
00:01:34,767 --> 00:01:35,567
Yes, dear.

20
00:01:35,700 --> 00:01:37,367
That's a promise, okay?

21
00:01:37,500 --> 00:01:41,333
We'll do everything so you
can go home that very day.

22
00:01:41,500 --> 00:01:42,733
Promise?

23
00:01:42,867 --> 00:01:43,533
Yes, child.

24
00:01:43,667 --> 00:01:44,367
I promise.

25
00:01:46,433 --> 00:01:47,133
Come on now.

26
00:01:47,267 --> 00:01:48,533
Stop crying.

27
00:01:48,667 --> 00:01:51,633
You've been crying for so long.

28
00:02:03,367 --> 00:02:05,433
You saw her condition.

29
00:02:07,267 --> 00:02:09,133
Her cell.

30
00:02:09,267 --> 00:02:10,967
What if...

31
00:02:11,100 --> 00:02:12,267
What if she gets sick in there?

32
00:02:15,433 --> 00:02:17,200
Her cellmates, too.

33
00:02:18,833 --> 00:02:20,100
You know, Coleen was right.

34
00:02:21,167 --> 00:02:23,333
We don't know what people
in there might do to her.

35
00:02:25,967 --> 00:02:28,967
All we can really do
is pray harder.

36
00:02:29,100 --> 00:02:30,533
Ask God to protect her.

37
00:02:35,600 --> 00:02:40,433
God is all we can cling
to at this moment.

38
00:02:43,467 --> 00:02:46,600
Are you sure, Manuel?

39
00:02:47,900 --> 00:02:53,433
You're really okay staying here
to keep Coleen company?

40
00:02:53,567 --> 00:02:56,633
Felma, there's nothing
I won't endure for our children.

41
00:03:00,333 --> 00:03:04,967
Thank you so much
for being here for us,

42
00:03:06,733 --> 00:03:08,367
even after we had an argument.

43
00:03:10,967 --> 00:03:15,833
I'm sorry for the things I said.

44
00:03:15,967 --> 00:03:19,167
And for not understanding you.

45
00:03:20,233 --> 00:03:22,633
Felma, believe me.

46
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:24,567
Didn't I promise you?

47
00:03:24,700 --> 00:03:27,533
We'll stay together
until the end.

48
00:03:27,667 --> 00:03:29,033
Until Coleen's name
is cleared...

49
00:03:29,167 --> 00:03:30,333
until she's free.

50
00:03:31,800 --> 00:03:33,867
Felma, I promise.

51
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:35,667
I'll do everything
to make that happen.

52
00:03:42,700 --> 00:03:43,533
<i> Delicious!</i>

53
00:03:43,667 --> 00:03:45,167
<i> This is so good.</i>

54
00:03:45,300 --> 00:03:46,867
<i> Mine!</i>

55
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:48,567
So good.

56
00:03:48,700 --> 00:03:49,767
<i> Thanks for this, Coleen.</i>

57
00:03:49,900 --> 00:03:52,067
You didn't tell us
you were rich.

58
00:03:52,200 --> 00:03:53,200
Yeah!

59
00:03:53,333 --> 00:03:56,167
You could probably feed
the whole neighborhood!

60
00:03:56,333 --> 00:03:59,900
Figures. People like them
have power.

61
00:04:00,033 --> 00:04:02,167
They'll use their money,
pull some strings.

62
00:04:02,300 --> 00:04:04,633
She'll walk free
even if she is guilty.

63
00:04:06,433 --> 00:04:11,067
Bella, I'm getting out
because I'm innocent.

64
00:04:11,200 --> 00:04:12,233
Not because of money.

65
00:04:12,367 --> 00:04:13,933
Not because of my family's
influence.

66
00:04:14,067 --> 00:04:15,700
Oh, wow!

67
00:04:15,833 --> 00:04:17,600
Cocky!

68
00:04:17,733 --> 00:04:23,800
Hey, while you're in here,
we're all equal!

69
00:04:23,933 --> 00:04:24,767
<i> Yeah!</i>

70
00:04:24,900 --> 00:04:25,733
<i> So full of yourself!</i>

71
00:04:27,133 --> 00:04:28,200
That looks tasty.

72
00:04:28,367 --> 00:04:30,933
-That's mine!
-Hey, Bella, don't be like that!

73
00:04:31,067 --> 00:04:32,233
It's good!

74
00:04:32,367 --> 00:04:33,433
<i> Coleen's new here.</i>

75
00:04:33,567 --> 00:04:34,433
Stop picking on her.

76
00:04:36,433 --> 00:04:37,400
So now you're butting in?

77
00:04:40,567 --> 00:04:42,267
Sorry, Coleen.

78
00:04:42,400 --> 00:04:44,200
Bella's always like that.

79
00:04:44,333 --> 00:04:46,467
She's been here the longest.

80
00:04:51,067 --> 00:04:52,467
- Let me see.
- Hey!

81
00:04:52,600 --> 00:04:53,633
Wait, that's mine!

82
00:04:53,767 --> 00:04:54,567
Just want to see!

83
00:04:54,700 --> 00:04:55,033
That's mine!

84
00:04:55,167 --> 00:04:57,267
Just looking!

85
00:04:57,400 --> 00:04:58,600
You're so stingy!

86
00:04:58,733 --> 00:05:00,500
While you're here,
learn how to get along!

87
00:05:03,167 --> 00:05:04,200
Just looking!

88
00:05:08,400 --> 00:05:09,800
Clothes for the rich.

89
00:05:12,733 --> 00:05:13,533
Pretty!

90
00:05:13,667 --> 00:05:14,967
This one's nice!

91
00:05:15,100 --> 00:05:17,400
- So pretty.
- Sexy, too.

92
00:05:17,533 --> 00:05:19,400
This looks good.

93
00:05:19,533 --> 00:05:20,600
What do you call this?

94
00:05:20,733 --> 00:05:22,167
A jumper?

95
00:05:22,300 --> 00:05:24,100
<i> Cute!</i>

96
00:05:24,233 --> 00:05:25,867
Perfect for me.

97
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:26,967
<i> Party outfit.</i>

98
00:05:37,333 --> 00:05:38,933
Miss Cruz, you have a visitor.

99
00:05:54,567 --> 00:05:55,733
How are you, Coleen?

100
00:05:57,500 --> 00:05:58,633
What are you doing here?

101
00:06:00,100 --> 00:06:02,400
Do you even know the penalty
for your crime?

102
00:06:04,200 --> 00:06:06,067
Reclusion perpetua.

103
00:06:07,967 --> 00:06:09,833
Life imprisonment.

104
00:06:12,067 --> 00:06:14,367
I'm getting out of here.

105
00:06:14,500 --> 00:06:16,067
Oh, yes.

106
00:06:16,200 --> 00:06:18,733
You'll get out to be transferred
to the City Jail.

107
00:06:18,867 --> 00:06:20,400
Because that's
where you will rot.

108
00:06:20,533 --> 00:06:21,800
That's where you will die.

109
00:06:21,933 --> 00:06:22,567
Friend!

110
00:06:28,367 --> 00:06:29,400
You killed my daughter!

111
00:06:29,533 --> 00:06:30,900
You killed Jessica!

112
00:06:31,033 --> 00:06:32,033
You killed her!

113
00:06:32,167 --> 00:06:33,033
You killed her!

114
00:06:33,167 --> 00:06:34,533
- You killed her!
- Let go of me!

115
00:06:34,667 --> 00:06:35,600
- You killed her!
- Let go of me!

116
00:06:35,733 --> 00:06:38,700
- You killed Jessica!
- I didn't kill Jessica!

117
00:06:39,667 --> 00:06:41,100
Let go of the girl!

118
00:06:43,767 --> 00:06:46,767
- You shameless monster!
- You're worse!

119
00:06:48,300 --> 00:06:50,100
I'm shameless?
You dare call me that now?

120
00:06:51,033 --> 00:06:52,967
Who here is the killer?

121
00:06:53,933 --> 00:06:55,033
You.

122
00:06:55,633 --> 00:06:59,833
- You killed my daughter!
- I did not kill Jessica!

123
00:06:59,967 --> 00:07:02,067
I didn't kill her!

124
00:07:02,200 --> 00:07:04,667
What do you mean
you didn't kill her?

125
00:07:04,800 --> 00:07:06,167
Admit it! Admit it now!

126
00:07:06,300 --> 00:07:07,100
Come on, say it!

127
00:07:07,233 --> 00:07:08,567
Admit it!

128
00:07:08,700 --> 00:07:10,233
- Stop it!
- That's enough!

129
00:07:10,367 --> 00:07:11,967
- Stop it.
- That's enough.

130
00:07:12,100 --> 00:07:14,600
- Ma'am, enough!
- Admit your crime!

131
00:07:14,767 --> 00:07:16,200
You killed my daughter!
Admit it!

132
00:07:16,333 --> 00:07:18,800
- Ma'am, stop!
- I'm innocent!

133
00:07:18,933 --> 00:07:21,200
Even if you hurt me
again and again...

134
00:07:21,333 --> 00:07:23,100
Even if you kill me...

135
00:07:23,433 --> 00:07:25,400
I won't confess
to something I didn't do!

136
00:07:25,733 --> 00:07:28,233
I'll keep saying it
over and over

137
00:07:28,367 --> 00:07:30,933
that I didn't kill Jessica!
Because that's the truth!

138
00:07:31,067 --> 00:07:35,433
And I could never do that
to my sister or to anyone!

139
00:07:36,867 --> 00:07:38,433
Oh, really?

140
00:07:38,567 --> 00:07:40,233
Fine.

141
00:07:40,367 --> 00:07:43,433
Keep denying it
until your last breath.

142
00:07:43,567 --> 00:07:47,733
Whatever you do, you're still
ending up in prison.

143
00:07:47,900 --> 00:07:49,567
If I were you,

144
00:07:49,700 --> 00:07:51,333
I'd start getting used to it.

145
00:07:51,467 --> 00:07:52,867
Because what
you're experiencing now?

146
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:55,767
This is just the appetizer,
Coleen.

147
00:07:55,900 --> 00:07:58,300
Do you know
what the main course is?

148
00:07:58,433 --> 00:08:00,200
City Jail.

149
00:08:00,333 --> 00:08:01,933
That's where you'll die.

150
00:08:02,067 --> 00:08:05,233
That's where you'll rot.
So good luck to you.

151
00:08:38,400 --> 00:08:40,367
What time is it?
Hazel's still not here.

152
00:08:47,733 --> 00:08:49,067
Who are those people?

153
00:08:50,433 --> 00:08:52,500
Looks like they're
waiting for someone.

154
00:08:56,700 --> 00:08:58,500
They're here!

155
00:08:58,633 --> 00:09:00,067
Miss Hazel,
do you have any comment

156
00:09:00,200 --> 00:09:03,133
now that another suspect,
Coleen Cruz, has been arrested?

157
00:09:06,100 --> 00:09:07,167
I'm just grateful.

158
00:09:07,300 --> 00:09:09,167
Ma'am, have you spoken to her?

159
00:09:12,333 --> 00:09:14,400
Talking to that girl is useless.

160
00:09:15,733 --> 00:09:17,800
She doesn't know how to...

161
00:09:17,933 --> 00:09:19,667
admit what she's done.

162
00:09:21,233 --> 00:09:22,600
Unlike Timo Malabanan,

163
00:09:24,067 --> 00:09:25,800
the man
who ran over my daughter.

164
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:28,100
Not only...

165
00:09:29,133 --> 00:09:30,933
did he apologize,

166
00:09:33,500 --> 00:09:35,700
but he confessed to his crime.

167
00:09:40,400 --> 00:09:42,667
Coleen Cruz should learn
from that.

168
00:09:43,733 --> 00:09:46,800
In your opinion, what are
the chances you'll win the case?

169
00:09:48,467 --> 00:09:50,233
I can only hope that...

170
00:09:52,100 --> 00:09:53,833
I win this case.

171
00:09:56,400 --> 00:09:58,267
For my daughter, Jessica.

172
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:03,233
I'm so grateful

173
00:10:03,400 --> 00:10:05,533
to the netizens,

174
00:10:05,667 --> 00:10:07,567
especially to the...

175
00:10:07,700 --> 00:10:10,033
parents like me.

176
00:10:11,167 --> 00:10:14,300
Your messages of support,

177
00:10:14,433 --> 00:10:15,733
love...

178
00:10:15,867 --> 00:10:18,733
yes, they reach me.
I read all of them.

179
00:10:19,867 --> 00:10:24,100
And they give me the strength
to keep fighting for Jessica.

180
00:10:24,233 --> 00:10:26,600
To get the justice
she deserves.

181
00:10:29,933 --> 00:10:32,100
What's that woman up to
this time?

182
00:10:33,933 --> 00:10:34,867
She's here.

183
00:10:36,067 --> 00:10:37,633
Look,
there's the suspect's mother.

184
00:10:45,100 --> 00:10:47,200
Miss Felma,

185
00:10:47,333 --> 00:10:49,367
you're Coleen Cruz's mother,
right?

186
00:10:49,500 --> 00:10:52,800
Ma'am, what can you say
about your daughter's arrest?

187
00:10:52,933 --> 00:10:54,167
I shouldn't...

188
00:10:54,300 --> 00:10:55,633
I have nothing to say.

189
00:10:56,633 --> 00:10:57,600
Please.

190
00:10:58,733 --> 00:11:01,467
- Let us through.
- Let her be.

191
00:11:01,600 --> 00:11:03,900
I'm sure she and my husband
are here

192
00:11:04,033 --> 00:11:05,367
to visit the suspect.

193
00:11:06,800 --> 00:11:08,933
Good for you.

194
00:11:09,100 --> 00:11:10,433
You get to visit
your daughter.

195
00:11:11,567 --> 00:11:12,933
Alive and well.

196
00:11:13,933 --> 00:11:15,267
While mine...

197
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:18,067
is gone.

198
00:11:18,200 --> 00:11:20,667
Dead because of your
daughter's wickedness.

199
00:11:21,700 --> 00:11:23,900
I don't know what game
you're playing, Hazel.

200
00:11:25,300 --> 00:11:28,067
You really called
these reporters?

201
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:29,133
For what?

202
00:11:30,367 --> 00:11:32,500
So they can feast
on my daughter?

203
00:11:32,633 --> 00:11:34,433
Felma, don't treat them
that way.

204
00:11:34,567 --> 00:11:36,267
Don't be paranoid.

205
00:11:36,400 --> 00:11:38,633
They're here to do their job.

206
00:11:38,767 --> 00:11:40,600
Reporting, that's their work.

207
00:11:41,533 --> 00:11:43,333
Should I stop them?

208
00:11:43,467 --> 00:11:45,000
Or are you just...

209
00:11:45,133 --> 00:11:47,700
ashamed that
the whole world knows

210
00:11:47,833 --> 00:11:50,000
your daughter killed my child?

211
00:11:52,200 --> 00:11:54,800
Felma, let it go.

212
00:11:54,933 --> 00:11:56,500
Manuel! Listen to yourself.

213
00:11:56,633 --> 00:11:59,467
You talk as if it were
Hazel who did something wrong.

214
00:11:59,600 --> 00:12:01,100
For the record,

215
00:12:02,433 --> 00:12:05,367
Coleen did not kill Jessica.

216
00:12:05,500 --> 00:12:08,067
The case is already in court.

217
00:12:08,200 --> 00:12:09,867
Why don't we all wait?

218
00:12:10,000 --> 00:12:12,100
Wait for the decision?

219
00:12:12,233 --> 00:12:17,300
Instead of you spreading
judgments and lies?

220
00:12:17,467 --> 00:12:19,167
Judgmental?

221
00:12:19,300 --> 00:12:21,567
My judgment is based on history.

222
00:12:23,333 --> 00:12:29,133
How many times did Coleen hurt
my daughter?

223
00:12:29,267 --> 00:12:31,633
Did you think
I didn't know...

224
00:12:31,767 --> 00:12:34,233
how cruel she was to Jessica?

225
00:12:34,367 --> 00:12:36,133
They already reconciled...

226
00:12:37,933 --> 00:12:40,933
after the accident.

227
00:12:41,067 --> 00:12:42,467
And you believed her?

228
00:12:43,567 --> 00:12:46,200
She only said that to escape.

229
00:12:46,333 --> 00:12:49,233
To avoid facing the consequences
of Jessica's death.

230
00:12:49,400 --> 00:12:50,767
Hazel, enough!

231
00:12:51,900 --> 00:12:53,167
Stop adding
to Coleen's suffering.

232
00:12:53,300 --> 00:12:55,467
The child is already in jail.

233
00:12:55,600 --> 00:12:57,967
And now you're destroying
her reputation to everyone?

234
00:12:58,100 --> 00:13:00,200
My daughter isn't perfect.

235
00:13:00,333 --> 00:13:02,000
She makes mistakes.

236
00:13:02,133 --> 00:13:06,533
But that's not enough reason
for people to demonize her.

237
00:13:06,667 --> 00:13:09,133
To bash her online...

238
00:13:09,267 --> 00:13:11,467
because of you
and what you're doing!

239
00:13:11,600 --> 00:13:13,800
And why should I care
about your daughter's feelings?

240
00:13:15,033 --> 00:13:16,667
What about me?

241
00:13:16,800 --> 00:13:20,133
Do you know how painful it is
for a mother...

242
00:13:20,267 --> 00:13:21,667
to lose a child?

243
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:25,600
To wake up one morning...

244
00:13:25,733 --> 00:13:28,700
thinking I'd still get to see
my daughter,

245
00:13:28,833 --> 00:13:30,700
only to realiz...

246
00:13:30,833 --> 00:13:32,533
she's gone.

247
00:13:32,667 --> 00:13:35,700
Gone forever. Never coming back.

248
00:13:35,833 --> 00:13:37,133
Because she's dead.

249
00:13:38,067 --> 00:13:40,967
And do you know
how painful it is...

250
00:13:41,100 --> 00:13:43,000
to have your own child
be blamed?

251
00:13:44,067 --> 00:13:46,600
Every day I worry
about Coleen.

252
00:13:46,733 --> 00:13:49,067
What she's feeling,

253
00:13:49,200 --> 00:13:51,300
if she's still thinking clearly,

254
00:13:51,433 --> 00:13:53,567
if she might hurt herself.

255
00:13:54,567 --> 00:13:58,433
It's like you're killing
my daughter, too...

256
00:13:58,567 --> 00:14:00,933
with what you are doing, Hazel.

257
00:14:01,067 --> 00:14:04,500
A lifetime in prison
isn't enough for her.

258
00:14:04,633 --> 00:14:06,367
What she deserves is...

259
00:14:06,500 --> 00:14:08,533
the death penalty.

260
00:14:08,667 --> 00:14:10,533
She should die.

261
00:14:10,667 --> 00:14:12,367
Or maybe...

262
00:14:12,500 --> 00:14:14,367
she should really die.

263
00:14:14,500 --> 00:14:15,867
You're a monster.

264
00:14:16,900 --> 00:14:18,833
You're so cruel.

265
00:14:20,533 --> 00:14:21,600
You're a demon.

266
00:14:30,167 --> 00:14:31,100
You have the nerve to hurt me?

267
00:14:31,233 --> 00:14:32,033
You animal!

268
00:14:39,833 --> 00:14:41,133
That's enough!

269
00:14:41,267 --> 00:14:42,300
- That's enough!
- Stop, Ma'am!

270
00:14:42,433 --> 00:14:43,700
That woman!

271
00:14:43,833 --> 00:14:44,833
She's the one at fault!

272
00:14:44,967 --> 00:14:45,433
You all saw it.

273
00:14:45,567 --> 00:14:47,000
She hit me first!

274
00:14:47,133 --> 00:14:48,467
I'm the victim here,

275
00:14:48,600 --> 00:14:50,133
and she's making it look like
I'm the one to blame?

276
00:14:50,267 --> 00:14:51,367
You all saw it, didn't you?

277
00:14:51,500 --> 00:14:52,433
I was only defending myself.

278
00:14:52,567 --> 00:14:53,467
She attacked me first!

279
00:14:53,600 --> 00:14:55,433
- Yes, Sir.
- Miss Felma slapped her first.

280
00:14:57,200 --> 00:15:00,900
Why should I even explain
myself?

281
00:15:01,033 --> 00:15:03,167
You've already made up
your minds!

282
00:15:03,333 --> 00:15:05,767
You'd rather believe this liar!

283
00:15:06,067 --> 00:15:09,133
Let the court decide
who's lying.

284
00:15:09,267 --> 00:15:12,867
If I were you,
instead of attacking me,

285
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:14,933
prepare yourself.

286
00:15:15,067 --> 00:15:19,400
Because Coleen
is not getting out.

287
00:15:19,533 --> 00:15:21,767
She will rot in prison.

288
00:15:21,900 --> 00:15:23,133
She'll grow old there.

289
00:15:23,267 --> 00:15:24,833
She'll die there.

290
00:15:35,633 --> 00:15:37,867
What?

291
00:15:38,000 --> 00:15:39,567
Why are you still here?

292
00:15:39,700 --> 00:15:40,833
The show's over.

293
00:15:43,900 --> 00:15:47,967
I'm sure you've got enough
material now

294
00:15:48,100 --> 00:15:50,033
to feast
on my daughter's misery.

295
00:16:04,567 --> 00:16:08,400
<i>What she deserves
is death penalty.</i>

296
00:16:08,567 --> 00:16:10,533
<i> She should die.</i>

297
00:16:10,667 --> 00:16:13,867
<i> She should really die.</i>

298
00:16:14,000 --> 00:16:15,533
Viral already?

299
00:16:15,667 --> 00:16:18,767
Detective XY really has
tons of followers.

300
00:16:18,900 --> 00:16:19,700
So, what now?

301
00:16:19,833 --> 00:16:22,467
Can't we stop that video
from spreading?

302
00:16:22,600 --> 00:16:23,600
I feel bad for Coleen.

303
00:16:23,733 --> 00:16:25,967
It's making her look
even more guilty.

304
00:16:26,100 --> 00:16:27,700
Even mom and dad...

305
00:16:27,833 --> 00:16:29,767
Actually, all of us
are affected.

306
00:16:31,300 --> 00:16:34,633
Why don't you give
an interview too?

307
00:16:34,767 --> 00:16:37,933
I know a content creator
who talks about family issues.

308
00:16:38,067 --> 00:16:40,533
You could defend your family.

309
00:16:40,667 --> 00:16:42,067
Defend Coleen.

310
00:16:42,233 --> 00:16:43,833
We could do that.

311
00:16:43,967 --> 00:16:46,233
But what if the issue
blows up even bigger?

312
00:16:46,367 --> 00:16:50,200
If we respond,
Hazel will respond back.

313
00:16:50,333 --> 00:16:51,733
Then we'll have to defend
ourselves again and again.

314
00:16:51,867 --> 00:16:52,900
And isn't that exactly
what Coleen doesn't want?

315
00:16:53,033 --> 00:16:54,933
That's why she went
on social media detox.

316
00:16:55,067 --> 00:16:56,567
It'll just get messier.

317
00:16:56,700 --> 00:16:59,967
So, should we just
let that witch win?

318
00:17:00,100 --> 00:17:02,900
But isn't it wrong
to do nothing?

319
00:17:03,033 --> 00:17:05,100
Auntie, if we fight back,

320
00:17:05,233 --> 00:17:07,133
what makes us different
from her?

321
00:17:07,267 --> 00:17:10,633
All we can do is hold on
to the truth.

322
00:17:12,333 --> 00:17:15,567
We prove in court that
Coleen is innocent.

323
00:17:15,733 --> 00:17:17,867
We clear her name.

324
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:19,267
Our name.

325
00:17:24,767 --> 00:17:26,267
<i> I'm the victim here!</i>

326
00:17:26,400 --> 00:17:27,933
<i>And she wants to make me look
guilty?</i>

327
00:17:28,067 --> 00:17:29,033
<i> You all saw it!</i>

328
00:17:29,167 --> 00:17:30,267
<i> I just defended myself.</i>

329
00:17:30,400 --> 00:17:31,500
<i>- She hit me first!
- Yes, Sir.</i>

330
00:17:31,633 --> 00:17:33,433
<i> Miss Felma slapped her first.</i>

331
00:17:40,833 --> 00:17:44,033
Did you really have
to argue on camera?

332
00:17:44,167 --> 00:17:50,200
Mrs. Cruz, this kind of exposure
isn't helping your case.

333
00:17:50,367 --> 00:17:52,600
Once the proceedings begin,

334
00:17:52,733 --> 00:17:55,567
anything you say can be used
against you.

335
00:17:55,700 --> 00:17:57,200
You might even end up
getting charged yourself.

336
00:17:58,667 --> 00:18:00,967
Attorney, that's why
you're here.

337
00:18:01,100 --> 00:18:03,367
To defend me.

338
00:18:03,500 --> 00:18:05,433
Mrs. Cruz, yes,
but if you were in the wrong...

339
00:18:05,567 --> 00:18:09,000
But you're supposed to look
for what can justify my side.

340
00:18:09,133 --> 00:18:11,533
Can you not lecture me
right now?

341
00:18:11,667 --> 00:18:12,633
Just eat. Please.

342
00:18:17,700 --> 00:18:22,733
I'm only reminding you
to be careful with your actions.

343
00:18:22,900 --> 00:18:24,467
What's the issue now, Attorney?

344
00:18:26,000 --> 00:18:27,100
Felma's stressing me enough.

345
00:18:27,233 --> 00:18:28,133
And you're adding to it.

346
00:18:29,867 --> 00:18:31,767
I'll pay you if things
get complicated anyway.

347
00:18:33,267 --> 00:18:34,400
Timo's better than you.

348
00:18:34,533 --> 00:18:35,767
He's easy to control.

349
00:18:40,533 --> 00:18:41,200
Timo?

350
00:18:42,533 --> 00:18:44,767
The driver who hit Jessica?

351
00:18:46,400 --> 00:18:49,767
What do you mean he's
"easy to control"?

352
00:18:57,267 --> 00:19:01,300
Mrs. Cruz, does this mean
I was right all along?

353
00:19:01,800 --> 00:19:03,533
Did you really do
something to Timo?

354
00:19:03,667 --> 00:19:05,033
Relax!

355
00:19:05,167 --> 00:19:06,033
No, Attorney.

356
00:19:06,167 --> 00:19:07,667
I didn't do anything.

357
00:19:07,800 --> 00:19:09,200
How many times do I have
to tell you?

358
00:19:12,967 --> 00:19:14,100
All right. Fine.

359
00:19:14,233 --> 00:19:16,433
If you don't believe me,
what can I do?

360
00:19:16,800 --> 00:19:19,700
Go find evidence if you want.

361
00:19:20,000 --> 00:19:22,067
Prove whatever theory
you've made up.

362
00:19:25,100 --> 00:19:27,767
Mrs. Cruz, I'm warning you.

363
00:19:27,900 --> 00:19:30,300
If you did anything to Timo

364
00:19:30,467 --> 00:19:34,800
and you altered his testimony
in any way, that's perjury.

365
00:19:34,933 --> 00:19:36,567
It won't just be
Timo facing charges.

366
00:19:36,700 --> 00:19:38,000
You will, too.

367
00:19:38,133 --> 00:19:39,767
Let me also warn you.

368
00:19:39,900 --> 00:19:41,900
You don't get to scold me.

369
00:19:42,033 --> 00:19:43,633
You're supposed to protect me.

370
00:19:45,167 --> 00:19:49,733
Make yourself useful
and stop ruining my day.

371
00:19:58,267 --> 00:20:01,133
Dear, we brought
your favorite food.

372
00:20:02,900 --> 00:20:05,067
And your things
that you might need.

373
00:20:07,400 --> 00:20:11,467
Mom, I'm sorry.

374
00:20:11,600 --> 00:20:15,433
Hazel fought with you again
because of me.

375
00:20:15,567 --> 00:20:17,133
You're getting humiliated
because of me.

376
00:20:20,200 --> 00:20:23,667
Sweetie, you have nothing
to apologize for.

377
00:20:23,800 --> 00:20:25,667
You didn't do anything wrong.

378
00:20:28,467 --> 00:20:31,600
Dear, we should be
the ones apologizing.

379
00:20:31,733 --> 00:20:33,533
We couldn't get you out.

380
00:20:33,667 --> 00:20:37,167
If only we could've posted bail,
you'd be home right now.

381
00:20:37,333 --> 00:20:39,033
Hazel wouldn't be attacking you.

382
00:20:44,567 --> 00:20:45,967
Did she hurt you again?

383
00:20:51,667 --> 00:20:55,433
Mom, the slap and hair-pulling
don't bother me.

384
00:20:56,967 --> 00:20:59,100
I'm more scared
about what she said.

385
00:21:01,100 --> 00:21:02,067
Mom?

386
00:21:03,367 --> 00:21:04,133
Dad?

387
00:21:05,800 --> 00:21:07,933
Is what Hazel said true?

388
00:21:09,900 --> 00:21:11,867
Am I really not
getting out of here?

389
00:21:13,200 --> 00:21:14,933
She said I'll be transferred
to the City Jail

390
00:21:15,067 --> 00:21:19,267
and that I'll be there for life.

391
00:21:21,100 --> 00:21:23,867
Dear, that will not happen.

392
00:21:24,000 --> 00:21:24,833
Believe us.

393
00:21:24,967 --> 00:21:27,233
We promise you.

394
00:21:27,367 --> 00:21:29,467
We'll do everything
to defend you.

395
00:21:30,667 --> 00:21:36,667
Sweetheart, just trust
in God and in the law.

396
00:21:36,800 --> 00:21:39,900
We'll prove you're innocent.

397
00:21:41,133 --> 00:21:43,233
You will get out of here, dear.

398
00:21:43,400 --> 00:21:46,267
You'll return
to the life you had.

399
00:21:46,400 --> 00:21:48,467
That's our promise,
mine and your father's.

400
00:22:17,033 --> 00:22:21,033
Emmy, why am I like this?

401
00:22:23,033 --> 00:22:27,900
When mom and dad are here,
I feel encouraged.

402
00:22:29,833 --> 00:22:34,667
But the moment they leave,
the fear comes back.

403
00:22:35,867 --> 00:22:37,833
It is frightening.

404
00:22:37,967 --> 00:22:42,167
But at least you could fight
for the truth

405
00:22:42,300 --> 00:22:43,600
that you didn't do
anything wrong.

406
00:22:44,833 --> 00:22:46,133
Unlike me.

407
00:22:46,267 --> 00:22:48,100
I really did commit a crime.

408
00:22:48,233 --> 00:22:50,733
What did you do?

409
00:22:50,900 --> 00:22:52,300
I killed my uncle.

410
00:22:53,733 --> 00:22:56,467
I caught him raping my sister.

411
00:22:58,833 --> 00:23:00,233
Jackielou is just sixteen.

412
00:23:02,100 --> 00:23:07,000
I told my auntie about it,
but she didn't believe me.

413
00:23:07,133 --> 00:23:09,033
My sister has
a mental condition.

414
00:23:10,933 --> 00:23:12,867
They even said she might
have wanted what happened.

415
00:23:15,367 --> 00:23:17,633
I tried reporting it
to the police,

416
00:23:19,900 --> 00:23:22,600
but they chose to believe
my aunt and uncle instead.

417
00:23:22,767 --> 00:23:24,067
So...

418
00:23:24,200 --> 00:23:25,967
I took matters
into my own hands.

419
00:23:26,100 --> 00:23:30,033
I killed my uncle by hitting him
on the head.

420
00:23:30,167 --> 00:23:31,733
You may have done
something wrong,

421
00:23:34,533 --> 00:23:37,433
but because of it,
you saved your sister.

422
00:23:41,633 --> 00:23:42,600
Me?

423
00:23:44,467 --> 00:23:45,933
I didn't save Jessica.

424
00:23:49,400 --> 00:23:50,767
We had dreams, you know?

425
00:23:53,267 --> 00:23:56,133
We dreamed of opening
our own restaurant someday.

426
00:23:57,767 --> 00:23:59,967
We both loved cooking.

427
00:24:05,000 --> 00:24:08,400
But how am I supposed to
make that happen now?

428
00:24:08,533 --> 00:24:11,833
Coleen, you still can.

429
00:24:13,333 --> 00:24:16,400
Do it for both of you.

430
00:24:16,533 --> 00:24:19,167
Stay strong.

431
00:24:19,300 --> 00:24:21,600
Fight for the truth.

432
00:24:21,733 --> 00:24:24,433
That's the only way
you can save yourself.

433
00:24:31,500 --> 00:24:33,200
I hope I can do it.

434
00:24:38,033 --> 00:24:42,333
Coleen, I'm Jiro Gomez,
Reporter from PNTV42.

435
00:24:42,467 --> 00:24:45,467
My lawyer told me
not to speak to anyone.

436
00:24:45,600 --> 00:24:47,767
But this is your chance
to clear your name.

437
00:24:47,900 --> 00:24:50,567
Can you please
leave Coleen alone!

438
00:24:50,700 --> 00:24:52,067
They said Coleen
was granted bail.

439
00:24:52,200 --> 00:24:52,833
What?

440
00:24:52,967 --> 00:24:53,933
How is that possible?

441
00:24:54,067 --> 00:24:56,967
Mrs. Cruz, there are exceptions.

442
00:24:57,100 --> 00:25:00,233
And it depends on
the executive judge.

443
00:25:00,367 --> 00:25:02,033
Maybe they know
someone personally.

444
00:25:02,200 --> 00:25:03,000
Who?

445
00:25:03,133 --> 00:25:05,967
A certain Atty. Artemio Vital,

446
00:25:06,100 --> 00:25:07,967
the lawyer representing
Noah Salvador.

447
00:25:08,100 --> 00:25:09,700
Noah Salvador?

448
00:25:09,833 --> 00:25:10,633
- Coleen?
- Coleen!

449
00:25:10,767 --> 00:25:12,233
- Sweetheart!
- Mom, Dad!

450
00:25:12,367 --> 00:25:13,367
How did you get out?

451
00:25:13,500 --> 00:25:14,567
How did you get home?

452
00:25:14,700 --> 00:25:16,300
- Dad!
- Sweetheart!

453
00:25:21,633 --> 00:25:22,533
Noah?
